**`wrong_password_receives_error_and_connection_closes`** in `teamserver/tests/e2e_operator_agent_session.rs`:

1. Spins up a real teamserver via `spawn_test_server`
2. Connects a WebSocket client
3. Sends `OperatorMessage::Login` with the correct username (`"operator"`) but a wrong password hash
4. Asserts the server replies with `InitConnectionError` (not `InitConnectionSuccess`) — with a 5 s timeout to accommodate the server's 2 s failed-login delay
5. Asserts the server then closes the WebSocket connection

This covers the end-to-end rejection path that was previously only validated at the unit-test level in `auth.rs`.
