Done. Here's a summary of what was fixed:

**Bug**: `OperatorAgentInfo::process_path` was always set to `agent.process_name` (the basename, e.g. `explorer.exe`) instead of the full path the Demon agent sends over the wire (e.g. `C:\Windows\explorer.exe`).

**Root cause**: `AgentRecord` had no `process_path` field — only `process_name` (basename). The full path was parsed from the Demon init/checkin packet but then discarded after extracting the basename.

**Fix**:
1. Added `process_path: String` to `AgentRecord` in `common/src/domain.rs`
2. Added DB migration `20260315120000_agent_process_path.sql` (`ALTER TABLE ts_agents ADD COLUMN process_path TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''`)
3. In `demon.rs` and `dispatch.rs`, stored the full UTF-16 path in `agent.process_path` (alongside the basename in `process_name`)
4. Updated `database.rs` (`AgentRow`, INSERT, UPDATE) to persist/load `process_path`
5. Fixed `agent_events.rs` line 73: `process_path: agent.process_path.clone()` (was `agent.process_name.clone()`)
6. Updated all 9 `AgentRecord` test fixtures and added a regression test
