Done. Here's a summary of what was done for `red-cell-c2-rcy6`:

**Root cause**: `patch_payload()` had no upfront format check — it would write PE timestamps and image sizes into any binary, silently corrupting ELF files or truncated build artifacts.

**Fix** (`teamserver/src/payload_builder.rs:939`):
- Added a MZ magic check (`[0x4D, 0x5A]`) at the very start of `patch_payload()`, before the magic-bytes overwrite or any other modification
- Added an upfront call to `pe_offsets()` to validate the PE\0\0 signature (this function already validated it internally, but only when `compile_time`/`image_size` were configured — now it runs unconditionally)

**Tests added** (3 new):
- `patch_payload_rejects_non_mz_magic` — ELF-magic binary returns `InvalidRequest` with message containing "MZ magic"
- `patch_payload_rejects_empty_binary` — zero-byte input rejected before any read
- `patch_payload_rejects_invalid_pe_signature` — MZ magic present but `NE\0\0` instead of `PE\0\0`
